EENG 5316 - Optical Fiber Communication
An introduction to the analysis and design of fiber optic communication
systems. Electromagnetic wave propagation treatment in optical fibers
leading to single and multimode descriptions. Standard methods for
measuring fiber parameters, overall communication system performance
including sources and receivers.
Prerequisite: EENG 3303 and EENG 4312; prior coursework at the
undergraduate level in electromagnetic fields and communications
theory; or consent of instructor.
